 About NCR
NCR Corporation (NYSE: NCR) is a leading software- and services-led enterprise provider in the financial, retail, hospitality, telecom and technology industries. NCR is headquartered in Atlanta, Ga., with 34,000 employees and does business in 180 countries. NCR is a trademark of NCR Corporation in the United States and other countries.
Title: Senior Risk Management Analyst
Location: Atlanta, GA
Grade: 11
POSITION SUMMARY
<br/>
NCR is seeking an experienced risk management analyst to join a fast paced and stimulating work environment. We have global property, marine, D&amp;O and liability insurance programs with local placements in over 50 countries, in addition to a captive insurance company. We’re looking for an energetic, self-motivated, detail oriented individual with risk management experience in a global setting to join this two-person department.
KEY AREAS OF RESPONSIBILITY
Identify, evaluate, and provide risk management recommendations which help better manage the company’s business risks while minimizing the company’s overall cost of risk;
Establish exposure data, complete insurance applications and assist broker in the accurate development of insurance submissions;
Review all insurance binders, policies and endorsements for accuracy and completeness;
Act as company liaison with brokers, insurance carriers, TPA, and other vendors for issues related to the risk management program;
Develop and maintain relationships with regional and country finance personnel to communicate global insurance program coverage and financing arrangements;
Prepare required reports to maintain Ohio self-insurance and monopolistic state WC;
Review and interpret indemnification and insurance provisions in third party contracts to ensure compliance with Company policies and risk management best practices;
Assist company personnel with obtaining required insurance documentation (certificates of insurance, auto id cards) from broker/insurer or NCR intranet;
Serve as a technical resource to the global logistics organization for managing the company’s marine transit exposure and claims recovery process;
Ensure premiums, claim payments, and global invoices are issued timely and that they are properly paid, accrued and/or expensed;
Use financial systems to track expenses for budget analysis and to conduct account reconciliations;
Work with internal and external resources to document work processes to support SOX controls;
Leverage the company’s RMIS to provide data analytics that support safety, claim and insurance initiatives;
Establish a process to drive compliance, prioritization and accountability of the recommendations received from property engineering inspections;
Maintain internal Risk Management website to ensure that all insurance program and risk management information remains up-to-date and relevant;
Lead or support finance or risk management projects as required.
BASIC QUALIFICATIONS
Undergraduate degree in risk management, accounting, or related field
5+ years experience in risk management or related field
Excellent understanding of insurance markets, coverages, and broker relationships
Experience reading and interpreting contracts
Self-starting decision maker who can work independently
Excellent organizational and project management skills with attention to detail
PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS
Advanced Risk Management certifications and/or MBA
Excellent systems aptitude with strong excel and other financial or RMIS systems experience
Risk management and accounting experience in a global organization
Six sigma or process improvement experience
EEO Statement
